feat(incidents): wire UI for fault to ticket escalation

Backend already had POST /api/v1/tickets that creates a ticket linked
to a fault and auto-generates its SLA record, but the UI never exposed
it. There was no New-ticket button anywhere, so users could create
fault reports but not the tickets that track them.

Two ways to open a ticket now:

- From the fault row: extra menu item "Escalate to ticket" opens a
  dialog pre-filled with a priority derived from the fault severity
  (CRITICAL=P1, HIGH=P2, MEDIUM=P3, LOW=P4). Optional assignee.

- From the Tickets page: new "New ticket" button at top right opens
  a dialog with a dropdown of all non-CLOSED fault reports.

Backend creates the SLA record automatically: response due in 1h,
resolution due in 4h for P1, 24h for others.

Visible to ADMIN, MANAGER, NETWORK_ENGINEER.
